Project: CaféQueue – Booking and Queue Management App for Small Cafés and Restaurants

Description: Running a small café or restaurant means dealing with walk-in customers,
phone reservations, and peak-hour chaos all at once. We often lose track of who is
waiting, forget reservations, or turn away customers because we cannot estimate wait
times properly. We need a simple app that lets customers book a table or join a queue
from their phone, and helps our staff see who is coming, when, and how many seats we
need. It should be something our cashier or floor staff can use without any special
training, and something customers can access without downloading anything complicated.

General Needs & Background
Small café and restaurant owners often manage reservations through paper notebooks or
WhatsApp messages, which is unreliable and hard to track during busy hours. Customers
get frustrated waiting without knowing how long it will take. Staff waste time answering
the phone to take or confirm bookings. We want a system that reduces no-shows, keeps
the queue visible to everyone on shift, and lets customers feel informed and respected
even when it is busy. We do not want something expensive or complicated to set up —
just something that works on a tablet behind the counter and on customers' phones.

Relevant Stakeholders
Primary users: Café and restaurant owners, floor staff and cashiers, customers making
reservations or joining queues
Secondary users: Kitchen staff (to know incoming volume), delivery staff, café managers
reviewing daily booking history
Project stakeholders: Project team, course lecturer, small business advisors
Indirect stakeholders: Local business associations, food and beverage industry regulators,
payment and POS system providers

What We Want the App to Do
- Let customers book a table online or scan a QR code at the door to join the walk-in queue.
- Show staff a live view of the current queue and upcoming reservations on one screen.
- Send a simple notification to the customer when their table is nearly ready.
- Allow staff to mark a table as occupied, available, or reserved with one tap.
- Show an estimated wait time based on how many people are ahead.
- Let the owner set the number of tables and maximum party size.
- Keep a record of daily bookings so the owner can see busy hours.

Practical Limits We Are Working With
- Staff are not tech-savvy — the interface must be extremely simple.
- We cannot afford a subscription fee — the solution should be low cost or free to run.
- Most customers will use their own phones; we do not want them to install an app.
- The system should still work if the internet is slow (common in older shophouses).
- Must work on a basic Android tablet mounted near the register.

Evaluation Criteria
- Staff can manage the queue without calling us every five minutes.
- Customers stop asking "how long is the wait?" because the screen tells them.
- No-shows decrease because customers get a reminder.
- Booking history helps us plan staffing for weekends and holidays.